The Code

Copy and paste this into any Markdown file (README.md) or HTML page:

```markdown
[![Deploy to Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/img/deploy/button.svg)](https://app.netlify.com/start/deploy?repository=https://github.com/netlify-templates/one-click-hugo-cms)
```

But that's a generic template. For your specific Auch Na Mhor code, here is a custom deploy link with your HTML built in:

---

Your Custom One-Click Deploy Link

Click this link to deploy your site immediately:

👉 Deploy Auch Na Mhor to Netlify

Wait — Netlify needs your code in a GitHub repository first.

---

Correct Method (Still 2 minutes)

Here is the actual one-click experience:

Step 1: Create a GitHub repository

1. Go to github.com/new
2. Name it: auchnamhor
3. Make it Public
4. Click Create repository

Step 2: Upload your code

1. On the next screen, click "uploading an existing file"
2. Drag your index.html file
3. Scroll down and click Commit changes

Step 3: One-click deploy to Netlify

Click this button now:

https://www.netlify.com/img/deploy/button.svg

Replace YOUR_USERNAME in the URL above with your actual GitHub username.

Example: If your GitHub username is james, the link becomes:
https://app.netlify.com/start/deploy?repository=https://github.com/james/auchnamhor

---

Even Faster: Deploy Without GitHub

If you don't want to use GitHub, here is the drag-and-drop method (30 seconds):

Steps:

1. Save the code as index.html on your computer
2. Go to app.netlify.com/drop
3. Sign up with email (free, no credit card)
4. Drag your index.html file into the browser window
5. Done — your live URL appears immediately

That's it. No GitHub. No command line. Just drag and drop.

---

Your Live URL

After dragging and dropping, Netlify gives you a URL like:

· https://random-name-123456.netlify.app

You can rename it immediately:

· Go to Site settings → Change site name
· Enter: auchnamhor
· Your URL becomes: https://auchnamhor.netlify.app

